 FIND files by date
--------------------
 1) move all files older than 10 days to subfolder 'OLD'
   > find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -mtime +10 -exec mv {} OLD/ \;

 FIND files by size
--------------------
 1) list all files smaller than 10 bytes
   > find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -size -10c -print
 1) Delete all files smaller than 98 bytes
   > find . -maxdepth 1 -type f -size -98c -exec rm {} \;


 DELETE Files Older Than x Days
---------------------------------
https://tecadmin.net/delete-files-older-x-days

1. Delete all files older than 30 days in <directory>
  > find <directory> -type f -mtime +30 -exec rm -f {} \;

2. Delete Files Older Than 30 Days with '.log' extension
  > find <directory> -name "*.log" -type f -mtime +30 -exec rm -f {} \;


